General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (e) Administrative Support. – All administrative support and other services required by
2 the advisory council shall be provided by the School of Medicine of the University of North
3 Carolina at Chapel Hill.Department.
4 (f) Upon the recommendation of the Dean of the School of Medicine of the University
5 of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, Selection of Chair. – The Secretary shall select the chair of the
6 advisory council from among the members of the council. The chair shall serve in this position
7 until the expiration of his or her term.
8 (g) The chair shall convene the first meeting of the advisory council no later than October
9 1, 2015. Meetings and Quorum. – A majority of the council members shall constitute a quorum.
10 A majority vote of a quorum shall be required for any official action of the advisory council.
11 Following the first meeting, the advisory council shall meet at least quarterly. The advisory
12 council may meet more frequently upon the call of the chair or upon the request of a majority of
13 council members.
14 "§ 130A-33.66. Advisory Council on Rare Diseases; powers and duties; reports.
15 The advisory council shall have the following powers and duties:
16 (1) Advise on coordinating the Governor, the Secretary, and the General
17 Assembly on all of the following:
18 a. Coordination of statewide efforts for the to study of the incidence of
19 rare diseases within the State and the status of the rare disease
20 community.
21 b. Coordination of statewide efforts to increase public awareness and
22 understanding of rare diseases.
23 c. Identification of policy issues related to rare diseases and the
24 advancement of policy initiatives related to rare diseases at the State
25 and federal levels.
26 d. The appropriation of State funds to facilitate increased public
27 awareness of and improved treatment for rare diseases.
28 (2) Report to the Secretary, the Governor, and the Joint Legislative Oversight
29 Committee on Health and Human Services Services, and the Fiscal Research
30 Division on behalf of the General Assembly not later than January 1, 2016,
31 and annually thereafter, on the activities of the advisory council and its
32 findings and recommendations regarding rare disease research and care in
33 North Carolina, including any recommendations for statutory changes and
34 amendments to the structure, organization, and powers or duties of the
35 advisory council.
36 (3) In consultation with accredited medical schools, accredited schools of public
37 health, and hospitals licensed to operate in the State that provide care to
38 persons diagnosed with a rare disease, develop resources or recommendations
39 regarding quality of and access to treatment and services available within the
40 State for persons diagnosed with a rare disease.
41 (4) Advise and consult with the Department, the North Carolina Drug Utilization
42 Review Board, and the Medicaid Preferred Drug List Review Panel in
43 developing recommendations, resources, and programs relating to the
44 diagnosis and treatment of rare diseases.
45 (5) Identify additional relevant areas for the advisory council to study and
46 evaluate."
47 SECTION 2. Effective July 1, 2026, there is appropriated from the General Fund to
48 the Department of Health and Human Services the sum of two hundred fifty thousand dollars
49 ($250,000) in recurring funds beginning in the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be allocated to cover the
50 operating expenses of the Advisory Council on Rare Diseases authorized by Section 1 of this act.
